(21, 1, 3, 9, 'July', 'September', 'DST-V3I3P102', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/DST-V3I3P102', 'Tests for Checking the Computer Model of a Three-Phase Transformer or an Inductive Reactor and the Diagram for their Implementation', 9, 17, '[\"Pustovetov Mikhail\"]', '<p>This article proposes and substantiates a practical solution to the issue of determining the type of magnetic core of a three-phase transformer or reactor used in a mathematical model of the device. A three-legged single magnetic circuit is perhaps the most common due to its compactness. But, unlike other core configurations, it also provides strong magnetic links between the winding phases, which affects transient processes, including in unbalanced modes, as well as the ability to limit common mode currents. These circumstances are important for obtaining adequate simulation results.</p>', '[\"Common mode currents\",\"Inductive reactor\",\"Magnetic core\",\"Mathematical model\",\"Mutual inductance\",\"Simulation\",\"Three phases\",\"Transformer.\"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] Luís M.R. Oliveira, and A.J. Marques Cardoso, “Modelling and Simulation of Three-Phase Power Transformers,“ <i>Proceedings of the 6th International Conference on Modelling and Simulation of Electrical Machines, Converters and Systems (ELECTRIMACS 99)</i>, Lisbon, Portugal, vol. 2/3, pp. 257-262, 1999.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color:black;\">[</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Modelling+and+simulation+of+three-phase+power+transformers&amp;btnG=\" previewlistener=\"true\">Google Scholar</a><span style=\"color:black;\">] [</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://sapientia.ualg.pt/entities/publication/195dc55a-ae64-4a34-8d07-d785e283b605\" previewlistener=\"true\">Publisher Link</a><span style=\"color:black;\">]</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[2] Shivkumar V. Iyer, “Modelling and Simulating Transformers,” <i>Modeling and Python Simulation of Magnetics for Power Electronics Applications</i>, pp. 107-159, 2022.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color:black;\">[</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-96768-0_4\" previewlistener=\"true\">CrossRef</a><span style=\"color:black;\">] [</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=S+iyer%2C+Modelling+and+Simulating+Transformers.&amp;btnG=\" previewlistener=\"true\">Google Scholar</a><span style=\"color:black;\">] [</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-96768-0_4\" previewlistener=\"true\">Publisher Link</a><span style=\"color:black;\">]</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[3] Mitar Simić, Tomislav B. Šekara, and Srđan Jokić, “Model of Three-Limb Three-Phase Transformer Based on Nonlinear Open Circuit Characteristic with Experimental Verification,” <i>Telfor Journal</i>, vol. 6, no. 1, pp. 42-47, 2014.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color:black;\">[</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Model+of+Three-Limb+Three-Phase+Transformer+Based+on+Nonlinear+Open+Circuit+Characteristic+with+Experimental+Verification&amp;btnG=\" previewlistener=\"true\">Google Scholar</a><span style=\"color:black;\">] [</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://journal.telfor.rs/Published/Vol6No1/Vol6No1_A8.pdf\" previewlistener=\"true\">Publisher Link</a><span style=\"color:black;\">]</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[4] Alexandr Orlov et al., “Losses in Three-Phase Transformers at Load Balancing,“ <i>Revista Espacios</i>, vol. 38, no. 52, pp. 37-45, 2017.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color:black;\">[</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Losses+in+three-phase+transformers+at+load+balancing&amp;btnG=\" previewlistener=\"true\">Google Scholar</a><span style=\"color:black;\">] [</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"http://es.revistaespacios.com/a17v38n52/17385237.html\" previewlistener=\"true\">Publisher Link</a><span style=\"color:black;\">]</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5] V.A. Bosneaga, V.M. Suslov, “Modeling of Three-Phase Three Leg Transformer Devices for Engineering Calculations of Asymmetrical Modes for Different Schemes of Winding Connections,” <i>Problemele Energeticii Regionale,</i> vol. 22, no. 2, pp. 38-50, 2013.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color:black;\">[</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Modeling+of+Three-Phase+Three+Leg+Transformer+Devices+for+Engineering+Calculations+of+Asymmetrical+Modes+for+Different+Schemes+of+Winding+Connections&amp;btnG=\" previewlistener=\"true\">Google Scholar</a><span style=\"color:black;\">] [</span><a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://journal.ie.asm.md/ro/contents/elektronnyij-zhurnal-n-222-2013\" previewlistener=\"true\">Publisher Link</a><span style=\"color:black;\">]</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[6] V. Bosneaga, and V. Suslov, “Transformer Device for Flexible Connection of Asynchronous AC Power Systems Using Semiconducting Switching with PWM,” <i>2017 International Conference on Modern Power Systems (MPS)</i>, Cluj-Napoca, Romania, pp. 1