(37, 2, 5, 15, 'April', 'June', 'LLL-V1I1P101', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/LLL-V1I1P101', 'Emotional Academia and a Queer Feud', 1, 7, '[\"Anna Nygren\"]', '<p>This article reflects on the emotional aspects of reading through the queerness of life. Readings during childhood affect the queer child’s mind – when other queer references are absent, and literature becomes the only area that mirrors one’s desires. Those early readings do, this article argues, affect later views on what is a possible relationship, what is a fictional and artistic desire, and patterns of reading – including academic interests. The article uses an autoethnographical method to revisit the author’s early academic or essayistic writings and use the overlapping of literature and life as a way to understand queer desires and possibilities to think about oneself.</p>', '[\"Affect\",\"Feminism\",\"Nordic literature\",\"Reader experience\",\"Queer.\"]', '<p>[1] Sara Ahmed, <i>The Cultural Politics of Emotion, </i>Durham, Edinburgh University Press, 2004.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=The+Cultural+Politics+of+Emotion&amp;btnG=\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://edinburghuniversitypress.com/the-cultural-politics-of-emotion-772.html#:~:text=The%20Cultural%20Politics%20of%20Emotion%20develops%20a%20new%20methodology%20for,migration%2C%20and%20reconciliation%20and%20reparation\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[2] Sara Ahmed, <i>Queer Phenomenology: Orientations, Objects, Others, Durham</i>, UK: Duke University Press, 2006.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.1215/9780822388074\">CrossRef</a>] [<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&