><p>[18] Eve Kosofsky Sedgwick (ed.), <i>Novel</i><em style=\"color:rgb(32, 33, 34);\"><i> Gazing: Queer Readings in Fiction</i></em><i>, </i>Durham, UK: Duke University Press, 1997.</p><p>[19] Eve Kosofsky Sedgwick, <i>Touching Feeling: Affect, Pedagogy, Performativity, </i>Durham, UK: Duke University Press, 2003.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Touching+Feeling%3A+Affect%2C+Pedagogy%2C+Performativity&amp;btnG=\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p>[20] Maria&nbsp;Lang, <i>Mördaren ljuger inte ensam, </i>Stockholm, Sweden: Norstedts, 1949.</p><p>[21] Ann-Sofie Lönngren, <i>Queer ekokritik – exemplet Strindberg</i> in Kivilaakso, Ann-Sofie Lönngren &amp; Rita Paqvalén (ed.) <i>Queera läsningar</i>, Stockholm, Sweden: Rosenlarv, 2012.</p><p>[22] Toril&nbsp;Moi,<em style=\"color:rgb(32, 33, 34);\"><i> What Is a Woman? And Other Essays, </i></em><i>Oxford</i> University Press, 1999.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=What+Is+a+Woman%3F+And+Other+Essays&amp;btnG=\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://global.oup.com/academic/product/what-is-a-woman-9780198186755?cc=us&amp;lang=en&amp;\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[23] Toril&nbsp;Moi,<i>&nbsp;</i><em style=\"color:rgb(32, 33, 34);\"><i>Sexual/Textual Politics: Feminist Literary Theory, </i></em>2<sup>nd</sup> ed.<i> </i>Oxford University Press, 2002.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Sexual%2FTextual+Politics%3A+Feminist+Literary+Theory&amp;btnG=\">Google Scholar</a>]</p><p>[24] Toril Moi, <i>Revolution of the Ordinary: Literary Studies after Wittgenstein, Austin and Cavell, </i>Chicago, US: The University of Chicago Press, 2017.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Revolution+of+the+Ordinary%3A+Literary+Studies+after+Wittgenstein%2C+Austin+and+Cavell&amp;btnG=\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/R/bo26102346.html\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[25] Tove Solander, <i>Queerblivanden</i> in Kivilaakso, Ann-Sofie Lönngren &amp; Rita Paqvalén (ed.) <i>Queera läsningar</i>, Stockholm, Sweden: Rosenlarv, 2012.</p><p>[<a style=\"color:rgb(0, 176, 80);\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Sexual%2FTextual+Politics%3A+Feminist+Literary+Theory&amp;btnG=\">Google Scholar</a>]</p>', '2023-02-09', '2023-02-16', '2023-02-23', '2023-03-31', 'uploads/LLL/volume-1/issue-1/LLL-V1I1P101.pdf', '2025-09-25 12:53:52', '2025-11-17 11:51:01', 'published');
