(63, 3, 8, 26, 'July', 'September', 'AIR-V1I1P101', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/AIR-V1I1P101', 'Expert System to Help Doctors in the Process of Bacteriological Diagnosis with Pre-Laboratory Screening Diagnose Certain Negligible Diseases such as Pulmonary Tuberculosis in an Under-Equipped Country', 1, 10, '[\"Humberto Cuteso Matumueni\"]', 'This article presents a new program which helps doctors to make a bacteriological diagnosis of tuberculosis in under-equipped countries. According to the WHO\'s annual report in 2018, under-equipped countries are the most affected at 95%, particularly the South-East Asia region, with 44% new, and Africa at 28%. Due to the lack or insufficiency of doctors in the hospitals, they are confronted with many problems. To remedy this situation, a system based on knowledge and rules has been set up to help the doctor in the bacteriological diagnosis process with pre-laboratory screening for pulmonary tuberculosis. ', '[\"Bacteriological diagnosis\",\"Pre-laboratory\",\"Screening\",\"Pulmonary tuberculosis\",\"Expert system\"]', '<p>[1] Mireille Cleret, Pierre Le Beux, and Franck Le Duff, <span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50);\">\"Medical Decision Support Systems\"</span>,&nbsp;<em>Les Cahiers du numérique</em>, vol. 2, no.2 , pp. 125-154, 2001.&nbsp;</p><p>[<a href=\"https://www.cairn.info/revue-les-cahiers-du-numerique-2001-2-page-125.htm\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[2] Kary Främling,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50);\">\"</span><em>Les réseaux de neurones comme outils d\'aide à la décision floue</em>,<span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50);\"> \"</span> Rapport de D.E.A, Ecole Nationale Supérieure des Mines de Saint-Etienne, 1992.<strong> </strong></p><p>[<a href=\"http://www.cs.hut.fi/~framling/Publications/DEA.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[3] GeeksforforGeeks, Expert Systems, 2021. [Online]. Available:&nbsp;https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/expert-systems/</p><p>[4] R. Forsyth, <em>Expert Systems: Principles and Case Studies</em>, 2<sup>nd</sup> edition, Chapman and Hall, 1984.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[5] B.G. Buchanan, and E.H. Shortliffe, <em>Rule Based Expert Systems</em>: <em>The MYCIN&nbsp;Experiments of the Stanford Heuristic Programming Project</em>, 1984.</p><p>[6] KNCV Tuberculosis Foundation to Eliminate TB, The Hague, The Netherlands. [Online]. Available:</p><p>https://www.kncvtbc.org/uploaded/2017/11/PatientFR-11-2017.pdf</p><p>[7] Nutritional Care and Support for Patients with Tuberculosis. Geneva, World Health Organization, 2013.&nbsp;[Online]. Available: https://www.aidsdatahub.org/sites/default/files/resource/nutritional-care-and-support-patients-tb_0.pdf</p><p>[8] Stuart Russell, and Peter Norvig , <em>Artificial Intelligence : A Modern Approach</em>, ISBN 0-13-103805-2, 1995.</p><p>[<a href=\"https://aima.cs.berkeley.edu/algorithms.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[9] Cédric Villani et al., <em>Giving Meaning to Artificial Intelligence: for a National and European strategy. </em></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Giving+Meaning+to+Artificial+Intelligence%3A+for+a+National+and+European+strategy&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>]<em> </em>[<a href=\"https://medias.vie-publique.fr/data_storage_s3/rapport/pdf/184000159.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[10] Pascal Roques , and Franck Vallée,&nbsp;Uml 2 in Action from Needs Analysis to j2ee Design, p. 385,&nbsp;2004. [Online]. Availab&nbsp;le&nbsp;: https://books.google.co.in/books/about/UML_2_en_action.html?id=6YOhPQAACAAJ&amp;redir_esc=y</p><p>[11] Pierre-Alain Muller, and Nathalie Gaertner, <em>Modélisation objet avec UML</em>, Eyrolles, 1998.</p><p>[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Mod%C3%A9lisation+objet+avec+UML&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google&nbsp;Scholar</a>]</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[12] Jacob Cohen, “A Coefficient of Agreement for Nominal Scales,” <em>Educational and Psychological Measurement</em>, vol.&nbsp;20, no. 1, pp. 37-46, 1960.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1177/001316446002000104\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">]</span> [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=A+Coefficient+of+Agreement+for+Nominal+Scales&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/001316446002000104\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p><br></p>', '2023-04-07', '2023-06-12', '2023-06-27', '2023-07-07', 'uploads/AIR/volume-1/issue-1/AIR-V1I1P101.pdf', '2025-09-25 16:17:06', '2025-11-17 11:51:01', 'published');
