(160, 6, 19, 59, 'April', 'June', 'DSM-V2I2P103', 'https://doi.org/10.59232/DSM-V2I2P103', 'Limitations and Challenges When Deploying AI in the Education System', 22, 25, '[\"Vuong Pham\", \"Minh Phan\"]', 'Integrating Artificial Intelligence (AI) into education offers transformative potential, including personalized learning and administrative efficiency. However, this paper highlights six critical challenges that hinder effective implementation: (1) over-reliance on AI and undervaluation of human educators, (2) inadequate teacher training, (3) digital inequality, (4) concerns over data privacy and algorithmic bias, (5) increased risk of academic dishonesty, and (6) dependency on unvetted technology providers. Drawing on global and Vietnamese case studies, the article stresses the importance of contextual adaptation, equitable infrastructure, ethical safeguards, and continuous evaluation. The findings underscore that AI should not replace human educators but complement them through thoughtful integration supported by firm policy and pedagogy.', '[\"Artificial Intelligence (AI)\",\"Education technology\",\"Vietnam education system\",\"Digital inequality\",\"Data privacy.\"]', '<p>[1] Abdulrahman M. Al-Zahrani, “Unveiling the Shadows: Beyond the Hype of AI in Education,” <em>Heliyon</em>, vol. 10, no. 9, 2024. </p><p>[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1016/j.heliyon.2024.e30696\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Unveiling+the+shadows%3A+Beyond+the+hype+of+AI+in+education&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.cell.com/heliyon/fulltext/S2405-8440(24)06727-6\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[2] Stéphan Vincent-Lancrin, and Reyer van der Vlies., “Trustworthy Artificial Intelligence (AI) in Education: Promises and Challenges<em>,” OECD Education Working Pape</em>rs, 2020. </p><p>[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1787/a6c90fa9-en\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=Trustworthy+artificial+intelligence+%28AI%29+in+education%3A+Promises+and+challenges&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://www.oecd.org/en/publications/trustworthy-artificial-intelligence-ai-in-education_a6c90fa9-en.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[3] Samo Varsik, and Lydia Vosberg, “The Potential Impact of Artificial Intelligence on Equity and Inclusion in Education,” <em>OECD Artificial Intelligence Papers</em>, 2024. </p><p>[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1787/15df715b-en\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">CrossRef</a>] [<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0%2C5&amp;q=The+potential+impact+of+artificial+intelligence+on+equity+and+inclusion+in+education%2C%E2%80%9D&amp;btnG=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://ideas.repec.org/p/oec/comaaa/23-en.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Publisher Link</a>]</p><p>[4] UNESCO: Governments Must Quickly Regulate Generative AI in Schools, Press Release, UNESCO, 2023. [Online]. Available: https://www.unesco.org/en/articles/unesco-governments-must-quickly-regulate-generative-ai-schools</p><p>[5]Manos Antoninis et al.,<em> “Global Education Monitoring Report 2023: Technology in Education: A Tool on whose Terms?</em>,” UCL Discovery, UNESCO: Paris, France, 2023. </p><p>[<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.54676/UZQV8501\" rel=\"noopener noreferre