(173, 7, 20, 61, 'October', 'December', 'CE-V1I1P102', '', 'The Roles of Microfinance in the Development of Infant Industries: A Case Study of Ikorodu Local Government', 9, 14, '[\"Okeowo Idowu Adeniyi\"]', 'Critical attention was given to the role of microfinance in the development of infant industry. The study considers a case study of Ikorodu Local Government using primary data. It calls for urgent intervention through microfinancing in Ikorodu Local Government small firms to forestall the possibility of the collapse of some of these firms. The study recommended the protection of these infant industries using simple protection instruments. It recognized microfinance and infant industry development as a tool for economic growth. The article revealed that if microfinance banks can operate within a conducive environment, there will be an upsurge in business development in Nigeria.', '[\"Microfinance\",\"Infant industries\",\"Growth\",\"Development\",\"Firms.\"]', '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[1] Pedzinski Alexander, and Odoemenam Franklin, “The Role of Informal Microfinance and Cooperative in Poverty Alleviation and Economic Development,” <em>Cooperative Finance in Developing Economies</em>, pp. 40-53, 2012. </p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\">[<a href=\"https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=The+role+of+informal+microfinance+and+cooperative+in+poverty+alleviation+and+economic+development,+&amp;hl=en&amp;as_sdt=0,5\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">Google Scholar</a>] [<a href=\"https://d1wqtxts1xzle7.cloudfront.net/46832979/COOPERATIVE_FINANCE_IN_DEVELOPING_ECONOMIES-libre.pdf?1467042860=&amp;response-content-disposition=inline%3B+filename%3DCOOPERATIVE_FINANCE_IN_DEVELOPING_ECONOM.pdf&amp;Expires=1696934184&amp;Signature=gMPt9OsNhlU4PH2oJjUw34dPn7KyNtEoRsSh-PMxJbE5TqS2oxmRQaWCNN9qHhBT4W2mHiAlGWb5rccrKAGsDL5FP8gbRRW~cM0UypSvIp6RODVQAljNHQRxTYf3OVZWibIQlqahVmIDQFu~z0WGDTxA538eppgx0bHMO2vmOQnx8X8alvsP~Ihqq8Saw5~qT7FcAgHby